SIMPLE: peppermint
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peppermint
<hw>Pep"per*mint</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pepper</ets> + <ets>mint</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An aromatic and pungent plant of the genus
<gen>Mentha</gen> (<spn>Mentha piperita</spn>), much used in medicine
and confectionery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A volatile oil (oil of peppermint) distilled from
the fresh herb; also, a well-known essence or spirit (essence of
peppermint) obtained from it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A lozenge of sugar flavored with
peppermint.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Peppermint</b></col><cd> camphor. <fld>(Chem.)</fld> Same
as <er>Menthol</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Peppermint tree</b></col>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a name given to several Australian species of gum
tree (<spn>Eucalyptus amygdalina</spn>, <spn>Eucalyptus piperita</spn>,
<spn>E. odorata</spn>, etc.) which have hard and durable wood, and yield
an essential oil.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pepperoni</ent>⟦br⟧
